    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="675"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d675">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3516/8–3148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paddock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dairen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-31">August 31,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received October 2—11:06 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Rumor discussed locally that Consulate Dairen may close as result closing
                    Vladivostok post. This speculation stems from alleged Nanking Central News
                    broadcasts at 2100 and 2300 hours August 27 reporting Secretary of State news
                    conference that date.</p>
                <p>It appreciated if Embassy verify whether broadcasts mentioned this office.<note
                        n="6" xml:id="d675fn6">For reply, see telegram No. 62, October 12, 1 p. m.,
                            <ref target="#pg_796">p. 796</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Dept. Department pass Nanking 38.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paddock</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
